title: [JIT Script] Torch Tensor indexing throws "Builtin cannot be used as a value" in scripting mode.
body_html:
❓ Questions and Help

Torch Tensor indexing throws "Attribute lookup is not defined" in scripting mode.
I am just trying to access the first and last element of a tensor which throws the following exception

File ".../torch/jit/init.py", line 884, in init_then_register
self._create_methods(defs, rcbs)
RuntimeError:
builtin cannot be used as a value:

Please note that this issue tracker is not a help form and this issue will be closed.

  • Discussion Forum

body:
## ❓ Questions and Help
Torch Tensor indexing throws "Attribute lookup is not defined" in scripting mode. 
I am just trying to access the first and last element of a tensor which throws the following exception

  File ".../torch/jit/__init__.py", line 884, in init_then_register
    self._create_methods(defs, rcbs)
  RuntimeError: 
    builtin cannot be used as a value:
